		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=3509"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3509')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4426&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Flowing+Thought"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Just something I would like to bring up regarding flowing thought items and the necro class.</P><P>First, let's look at the benefits of a flowing thought item to the following classes:</P><P>#1 Cleric:  Since healing is one of the most important components to any successful raid, it is very likely that any cleric-wearable flowing thought item will be considered for clerics first.  Taking into account that with clarity 3 the clerics gain 17 mana per tick, a ft3 item will give nearly 18% increase in mana regeneration.</P><P>#2 Wizard:  Wizards get very little innate mana regen, so again, every bit helps.  18% increase over ft3.</P><P>#3 Magician:  Ditto.</P><P>So far, all the previous classes have gained a substantial benefit.</P><P>Let's skip down to the bottom of the list:</P><P>#86,364 Necro:  Since our mana regen with Arch Lich is 35/tick, giving us the highest rate of regeneration in the game (approximately twice that of c3), Verant has had the foresight to make out most useful spells have double the mana requirement of most other similar damage spells.  For example, the wizard spell ice spear does 1200 dmg with 300 mana (instantaneously mind you) giving a damage to mana ratio of 4:1.  The mage spell shock of fiery blades is 1005 dmg for 334 mana, with a 3:1 ratio.  Now necro:  our best dd spell of 720 for 405 gives a ratio of only 1.7:1.  But you say "yes, but the spell does 2 things at once, both damaging the mob and healing you."  Absolutely true, but the healing part is to make up for the health loss we incur during mana generation.  So in the end, with Verant's careful thought, they DID balance the necro class.  Let me restate that, THE NECRO CLASS is BALANCED in regard to mana regeneration + damage + healing.</P><P>However... due to the nature of the huge mana regeneration we get, which is in the end eventually paid for by the loss of hitpoints which we must recover in lifetaps, a flowing thought item has just been reduced to 1/2 effectiveness for the necro class.</P><P>In other words, a flowing thought 4 item is as beneficial for us as a ft2 item is for nearly every other class due to the necro's mana regeneration.</P><P>So what am I saying with all this?  You decide.</P><P> </font></td>

      </tr>

