         actually boo you're wrong...  this is a game of percentages and streghts relative to one another.</P><P>Lets say verant increased all melee damage output across the board by 100DPS.  Under your logic that melees would be balanced with each other.  However it is not, because the difference in rogue DPS vs warrior DPS would narrow as a percentage.  Warriors would go from doing 75% rogue damage, to more like 90%.</P><P>In the same way, if your whole raid had acess to FT 15 items this would be almost a 50% increase in mana for clerics, but only 10-15% for necroes and shaman.</P><P>However, almost all FT is not all that great.  FT 5 gives a cleric 1 extra complete heal every 8 minutes.  If that's going to make or break your raid you have problems.  An items with good other stats should never be defaulted to clerics just because it had FT on it.</P><P><img src="http://www.mnickey.com/zon_sig.gif" border=0><BR>-Zondro Devilldoll 60 GWARLOCK of Karana<BR>(VERY BAD)<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21774" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21774</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
