        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=35351&amp;TOPIC_ID=4426&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Flowing+Thought&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Actually alot of the upgraded luclin items with FT do have very good hp bonuses.</P><P>It all depends on your play style.  Some people like hp and sacrifice everything for it.  Some people would rather have mana regen.</P><P>The fact is, you need to swap items around depending on the raid situation.  Max hps is kinda stupid if your fire res is below 100 on an AE wurm in tov b/c you will get hit for full every wave.  So you need to swap items around and keep a balance.  At the same time, keeping high res while solo is stupid.  </P><P>At least as far as my play style, mana always determines the rate at which i kill things when solo.  Having regrowth does not affect the number of mobs I kill per unit time when solo.</P><P>Try duoing with a bard vs a shaman.  Having mana song lets you kill far more things than regrowth does.</P><P>Warlock <BR>Unity, Prexus<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
