        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I know this is off topic but I'd partner with a shammy before I'd partner with a bard.  Shammys add exactly what we're lacking.  Their DoTs are higher versions of the DoTs we don't use much, they have great slows, torpor's da bomb and they generate more aggro than we do a lot of times and have the ac to back it up.  We give them what they're lacking wich is DPS via pet and we provide other utility like Zevfeer's.  A lot of shamans complain that they don't like to solo a lot because it takes them too long to kill stuff.  I seriously doubt I could have killed 4 of those alien things in Akheva at once with a bard and never be in trouble.  Shamans &gt; bards for partnering.</P><P>Anyways, when I am soloing normal mobs, health is the limiting factor.   I break even on mana with the stuff I kill unless I have to heal myself.  Regen &gt; FT and no we can't have it all.  <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle>  Most of us have to choose what's more important to us.  There are a lot of nice high end FT items with sweet health but the FT items I see on a daily basis don't have such nice health.  Every once in a while a nice FT item with great health rolls allong and there is no way I'd pass that up.  <img src=icon_smile_tongue.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
