         I hate torpor.  Who needs to be snared.  You can kill 3 centis easily by yourself in akheva. I do it quite regularly when i get an add on 2. Those things resist nothing and root lasts forever and a day on them. 4 is not a big jump if you have a whole other person helping you.</P><P>Exactly how many dots are you going to land on something if you are in a duo?   If you are using a pet, a snare (epic if you got it), splurt, and pyro or blood is pretty much sufficient or overkill for most experience mobs.</P><P>If you xp leisurely then sure, regen and hp is useful. You are liching lots and your mana is nearly full by the time you kill. But if you are killing multiple mobs as fast as you can, then mana is limiting.  More mana = faster kill rate for casters, unless you get whacked all the time.  </P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
