         &gt; Now you consider a raid having 8-10 clerics with an extra cheal every <BR>&gt; 8 minutes, that is HUGE.</P><P>A few mages producing an extra mod rod every minute or so would be bigger, and in general is much cheaper to achieve than giving 10 clerics ft5. High level raids are so focused around modrod-&gt;cleric-&gt;warrior anymore it's become kind of silly.</P><P>Obviously there's more too it, the rest of the raid has to maintain a certain DPS to make sure the mob actually dies, but in an ideal situation (no lag, no missed heals) two or three mages could easily keep clerics going for an indefinite period.</P><P><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
