        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Sure I COULD kill 3 at once if I really wanted to but how long would your down time be?  The point is to kill as fast as you can with zero down time.  I have zer down time with the shaman.  I don't DoT much.  Just a few splurts and snare.  Otherwise I just chain click my bracer and Zevfeer's once in a while.  Those 4 mobs died fairly fast with zero down time afterwards.  A large mana pool lets you kill more mobs at once or more at a faster rate to OOM but what good is that?  Unless you log in, plan to kill for 15-20 mins then go off and do something else.  The point is to kill something and by the time it's dead be at where you were when you started killing it.  So you can kill forever without stopping unless you run out of stuff to kill.</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
