        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=35429&amp;TOPIC_ID=4426&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Flowing+Thought&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>At least as far as my play style, mana always determines the rate at which i kill things when solo. Having regrowth does not affect the number of mobs I kill per unit time when solo.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Then you're soloing all wrong.  Your primary source of damage should never be lifetaps, they are our most inefficient source of damage.  Hell even the darkness line does better damage for the mana than taps.  Taps are there to replenish HP you lose from hits/lich.</P><P>Pyre: 2160 damage for 450 mana.  4.8 damage per mana.<BR>Pyro: 1998 for 400 mana. 4.995 damage per mana.<BR>Splurt:  1600 damage for 237 mana.  6.75 damage per mana.</P><P>Touch of Night: 720 damage for 405 mana.  1.78 damage per mana.<BR>Deflux:  330 damage for 198 mana. 1.67 damage per mana.<BR>Vexing:  1098 damage for 495 mana.  2.21 damage per mana.<BR>Bond: 720 damage for 360 mana. 2 damage per mana.</P><P>Just look at these ratios.  Until you equalize lich, every point of HP regen is worth *THREE* points of mana regen.  How ironic (and idiotic?) that Verant charges us 3 AA points for 3HP/tick and 12 for 3mana/tick.</P><P>Try using your efficient spells, you'll find an individual mob dies a bit slower, but over an hour, you'll kill many many more mobs because you'll always have mana.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Have you ever fought for more than 30+ minutes on a single mob ?<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Burrower Beast is the only thing I can think of (that I've fought) off hand that takes 30 minutes to kill.  The same thing applies there, let him cook with your dots...if you aren't the only necro there and you have to chain ToN as your damage, don't waste the other half of the spell...pick up a mod2...bound to be a huge pile.  If the wizards can do it, why can't we?  Despite its inefficiency manawise, it is 80 damage per second, which is nothing to sneeze at.  No amount of flowing thought is going to keep up your mana while you're burning it off as fast as you can.  That's what mods are for!</P><P>-Saleem<BR>Warlock of Xegony<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=183649" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=183649</a></P><P><BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
